  "title": "Supervisor, Engineering",
  "description": "<p><strong>Main Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>•\tSupervise and track welding technical requirements for process pipelines, installation requirements for fire protection pipelines, and on-site safety management standards.</p><p>•\tConduct regular quality inspections of construction work, summarize and address identified issues promptly, provide regular training on construction quality requirements, and ensure compliance with construction techniques.</p><p>•\tOrganize equipment and material acceptance at the Singapore site per headquarters requirements, and conduct comprehensive training to ensure new employees are proficient.</p><p>•\tOrganize technical personnel to verify P&IDs (Piping and Instrumentation Diagrams) after equipment installation, record and communicate findings to relevant departments and personnel.</p><p>•\tActively participate in Factory Acceptance Testing (FAT) and Site Acceptance Testing (SAT) of process and utility equipment.</p><p>•\tSupport and participate in the commissioning and testing of production workshop equipment, perform document reviews, registration, and archiving to ensure records are timely, accurate, and complete.</p><p>•\tOptimize equipment commissioning procedures, provide training, ensure strict adherence, promptly report issues, and proactively resolve them.</p><p>•\tManage safety during commissioning work, adhere to safety department regulations for special operations, and ensure construction and work safety.</p><p></p><p><strong>Competencies:</strong></p><p>•\tAssociate degree or higher.</p><p>•\tBackground in Mechanical Design, Manufacturing, or Automation.</p><p>•\tProficient in office software operations.</p><p>•\tOver ten years of experience in workshop equipment commissioning in CDMO industry.</p><p>•\tStrong communication and coordination skills.</p><p>•\tAbility to make independent judgments and solve problems.</p><p>•\tProficient in using MS Office software.</p><p>•\tStrong logical analysis abilities, capable of quickly assessing and managing situations.</p><p>•\tStrong time management skills, with a planned approach to work.</p><p>•\tClear cost awareness, with the ability to handle significant work pressure.</p><p>•\tProficient in reading and writing in both English and Chinese, capable of fluent technical communication with both the local Singapore team and the technical team in China.</p><p></p><p></p>",
